[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Understand Video jZP6Rq1CMdg View Based on the video analysis and your requirements for a no-fluff, tactical 7-day ad setup for ShineOn jewelry message cards, I'll create a precise action plan. Let me also gather more current information about Facebook ad setup and strategies. Using Tool | Search Facebook ads setup 2024 jewelry print on demand complete guide View Now I'll create your complete 7-day tactical Facebook ads setup plan based on Chris's proven $5 filter method from the video and current best practices. 7-DAY FACEBOOK ADS TACTICAL SETUP PLAN FOR SHINEON JEWELRY CAMPAIGN OBJECTIVE: Test products efficiently with minimal budget while identifying winners for scale DAY 1: FOUNDATION & FIRST CAMPAIGN SETUP STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\tAds Manager Access Check\tFacebook Business Account + Payment Method\tActive Ads Manager Dashboard\tEssential foundation - 95% of failures start here 2\tPixel Verification\tWebsite URL\tPixel firing correctly on product/collection pages\tRequired for data collection - Chris emphasizes data-driven decisions 3\tCampaign Structure Setup\tProduct 1 (specific design + phrase)\t1 Campaign = 1 Product\tChris method: One campaign per specific product/design combo 4\tBudget Configuration\t$10 total budget\t2 Ad Sets @ $5 each (ABO method)\tChris proven: ABO forces equal spend for proper testing 5\tTargeting Setup - Ad Set 1\tAge demographic analysis\tBroad targeting: Ages 35-60 (married likely)\tChris insight: Avoid \"married\" targeting - most don't declare it 6\tTargeting Setup - Ad Set 2\tInterest research\tInterest-based: Olive Garden OR Disney Parks\tChris strategy: Target activities married couples/families do 7\tCreative Upload\tHigh-quality product image\tClean, clear product focus + \"Personalize with any name\" text\tChris rule: Simple, clear product visibility - no busy backgrounds 8\tCampaign Launch\tFinal review\tCampaign LIVE by 11 AM\tChris critical: Launch in morning to avoid Facebook evening bugs DAY 1 BUDGET: $10 | EXPECTED SPEND: $10 DAY 2: FIRST EVALUATION & OPTIMIZATION STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\tPerformance Check (Morning)\t24hr data from Day 1\tCost Per Link Click (CPLC) analysis by ad set\tChris filter: CPLC is the #1 success predictor 2\tDecision Point 1\tCPLC > $2.00 on any ad set\tTurn OFF underperforming ad sets\tChris rule: No exceptions - bad CPLC = no scale potential 3\tDecision Point 2\tCPLC < $2.00 + good performance\tContinue running winning ad sets\tProven threshold from video analysis 4\tNew Campaign Launch\tProduct 2 (different design/phrase)\tSecond campaign structure\tChris principle: Test multiple products simultaneously 5\tTargeting Variation\tDifferent audience angles\tAge + different interest combinations\tDiversify audience testing per Chris methodology 6\tBudget Maintenance\tMonitor spend pacing\tEven $5 distribution per ad set\tABO method requires monitoring for equal spend DAY 2 TARGET: CPLC < $1.50 | CUMULATIVE BUDGET: $20 DAY 3: EXPANSION & REFINEMENT STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\t48hr Performance Review\tAll campaign data\tIdentify trends and patterns\tChris method: Look for consistent performance 2\tLaunch Campaign #3\tProduct 3 (third test)\tThird campaign running\tDiversification strategy - don't put all eggs in one basket 3\tAudience Split Testing\tWinning ad sets from Days 1-2\tTest 3rd ad set with different targeting\tChris example: Craft beer vs NASCAR vs Heavy Industry 4\tCreative Variation Test\tSame winning product\tAdd 2nd creative to best performing ad set\tTest creative impact on performance 5\tAdd-to-Cart Analysis\tFacebook Analytics\tATC data (note: Chris warns data is unreliable)\tUse as supporting metric, not primary decision maker DAY 3 TARGET: Identify 1 potential winner | CUMULATIVE BUDGET: $30 DAY 4: SCALE PREPARATION & DECISION POINT STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\t$40 Spend Evaluation\tCampaign total spend data\tMake kill/continue decisions\tChris rule: $40 campaign spend = major decision point 2\tWinner Identification\tSales + CPLC < $2\tMove to confirmation stage OR kill campaigns\tChris method: Both metrics must align 3\tConfirmation Stage Setup\tWinning ad set data\tIncrease budget to $15 (morning only)\tChris scaling: 5→15 budget increase for confirmation 4\tAudience Expansion\tWinning audience insights\tAdd similar interests to new ad sets\tBuild on winning audience data 5\tLoser Elimination\tPoor performing campaigns\tTurn OFF campaigns with no sales + bad CPLC\tChris discipline: Cut losses at $40 mark 6\tProduct Iteration\tLosing phrases/designs\tTest same phrase on different product types\tChris strategy: Good phrase, different product DAY 4 CRITERIA: Sale + CPLC <$2 = Scale | No sale + $40 spent = Kill DAY 5: CONFIRMATION STAGE & SCALING STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\tMorning Budget Increase\tConfirmed winner from Day 4\tScale budget 15→25 dollars\tChris timing: Critical morning-only scaling 2\tPerformance Monitoring\tScaled campaign metrics\tMaintain profitability + good CPLC\tEnsure scaling doesn't break performance 3\tNew Product Testing\tProducts 4-5 launch\tFresh testing campaigns\tContinue pipeline - Chris: 2% of products = 98% of profits 4\tAudience Documentation\tWinning audience data\tCreate audience personas\tBuild customer avatar from successful targeting 5\tCreative Optimization\tWinning creative analysis\tA/B test variations of winner\tOptimize successful elements 6\tProfit Analysis\tCost per purchase calculation\tDetermine true profitability\tChris rule: Profitable + good CPLC = real winner DAY 5 TARGET: $100-150 total spend on winner | Confirm scalability DAY 6: SIMPLE SCALING METHOD STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\tScale Decision Point\t$100-150 total spend + profitable\tEnter Simple Scaling Method\tChris method: Proven spending threshold 2\tBudget Increases\tWinning ad set performance\tScale: 25→50→75 (20-30% daily increases)\tChris rule: No doubling after $150 budget 3\tAdditional Ad Set Creation\tSuccessful targeting data\tAdd 2-3 more ad sets (max 5 total)\tChris limit: Maximum 5 active ad sets per campaign 4\tAudience Overlap Check\tMultiple ad set audiences\tEnsure minimal audience overlap\tFacebook algorithm prefers distinct audiences 5\tPerformance Monitoring\tScaled metrics\tWatch for performance degradation\tChris warning: Simple scaling can suddenly tank 6\tBackup Campaign Creation\tWinning campaign data\tDuplicate campaign as backup\tPrepare for potential tank scenarios DAY 6 TARGET: Scale to $75-100/day on winners | Max $2,500 potential DAY 7: OPTIMIZATION & FUTURE PLANNING STEP\tACTION\tEXPECTED INPUT\tEXPECTED OUTPUT\tRATIONALE/DATA 1\tWeek Performance Analysis\tAll campaign data\tROI, ROAS, profit analysis\tDetermine true winners and strategy refinement 2\tScaling Continuation\tConfirmed winners\tContinue 20-30% daily increases\tChris method: Gradual scaling for sustainability 3\tNew Product Pipeline\tProduct research\tNext week's testing products identified\tChris principle: Constant product testing required 4\tCustomer Avatar Refinement\tWinning audience data\tDetailed buyer personas\tUse successful targeting for future campaigns 5\tCreative Asset Development\tWinning creative analysis\tDevelop variations and new creatives\tBuild creative library from winners 6\tProfit Reinvestment Strategy\tWeek 1 profits\tPlan for Week 2 budget allocation\tScale winners, test new products DAY 7 TARGET: Identify 1-2 scalable winners | Plan Week 2 strategy CRITICAL SUCCESS METRICS & DECISION POINTS Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) METRIC\tDAY 1\tDAY 2\tDAYS 3-4\tDAYS 5-7\tACTION Cost Per Link Click\t<$2.00\t<$1.50\t<$1.00\t<$0.75\tPrimary success indicator Campaign Spend\t$10\t$20\t$40\t$100-150\tDecision thresholds Purchase Conversion\tOptional\tPreferred\tRequired\tRequired\tCombined with CPLC Add to Cart\tIgnore\tMonitor\tUse as signal\tProfit focus\tSupporting metric only Decision Framework Copy IF CPLC > $2.00 → KILL AD SET IF Spend = $40 + No Sales + Bad CPLC → KILL CAMPAIGN IF Sales + CPLC < $2.00 → SCALE TO CONFIRMATION IF Profitable + CPLC < $1.00 → ENTER SIMPLE SCALING ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS FOR COMPLETE SETUP To execute this plan effectively, I need: Product Information: Specific jewelry designs/phrases you're testing Product margins and pricing Collection page URLs Individual product page URLs Technical Setup: Facebook Business Manager access level Pixel implementation status Shopify/website integration details Payment processing setup Creative Assets: High-quality product images (clean backgrounds) Video content (if available) Message card examples Personalization examples Targeting Research: Competitor analysis Customer demographics (if available) Interest categories relevant to your designs Chris's Core Philosophy: \"A winning product reveals itself. Don't fight the data. Be a card counter, not a gambler.\" This tactical plan follows Chris's proven $5 filter method that has generated millions in POD revenue. The key is discipline - stick to the metrics, cut losses quickly, and scale winners aggressively. Would you like me to create specific targeting audiences or develop creative guidelines based on your actual products? Super Agent Your AI Employee Free Now +13 Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=28e410d9-a3ed-4d37-8ae9-0b5c8fa98129","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=28e410d9-a3ed-4d37-8ae9-0b5c8fa98129"}]}]}]
